Fox Energy Center's management is committed to supporting the emergency response organization and its prescribed functions. Emergency response team members are drawn from the existing employee pool and the organizational concept fosters pride and emphas concerns for safe operation of the facility. The well-defined emergency response organization operates in conjunction with the Kaukauna Fire Department and the Outagamie County LEPC to alleviate safety concerns about handling aqueous ammonia.



Auditing Program

The facility has developed an auditing program for the ammonia system. This audit program includes elements from the Program 3 requirements and has been established to provide a mechanism for periodic reviews of the various aspects of the RMP including:



-the physical ammonia system;

-hazard review;

-operation of the system;

-maintenance procedures;

-training procedures; and

-incident investigation procedures.



Although not specifically required by the RMP regulations for Program 2 facilities, audits are conducted every three years. A copy of the audit form used to conduct these audits is included in this document.



Incident Investigation Program



Fox Energy Center has developed an incident investigation program for the facility's ammonia system. This program includes elements from the Program 3 requirements and has been established to provide a mechanism for determining root causes of accidental releases of ammonia and preventing such events in the future. A copy of the form used to conduct incident investigations is included in this document.
